{"word":"μάθημα","slug":"μάθημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μάθημα</b></el> <el>(μάθημα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μανθάνω'><el>μανθάνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that which is learnt, a lesson</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>learning, knowledge, science</i>, <a href='S:often'>oft.</a> in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>the mathematical sciences</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}